45\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"MBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0022230 {source=\"MBA\"} ! retrohippocampal region\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035972\nname: interanterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus\ndef: \"A group of nerve cells that bridges the midline of the thalamus between the anterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus of the left and right sides. According to Crosby (1962), it is more developed and consistently present in rodents than in primates (adapted from Brain Info).\" [NLX:144468]\nsynonym: \"IAD\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [MBA:1113]\nsynonym: \"interanterodorsal nucleus of thalamus\" RELATED [NLX:144468]\nsynonym: \"interanterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1273]\nsynonym: \"interanterodorsal nucleus thalamus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1273]\nsynonym: \"interanterodorsal thalamic nucleus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1273]\nsynonym: \"nucleus commissura interanterodorsalis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1273]\nsynonym: \"nucleus interanterodorsalis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1273]\nxref: MBA:1113\nxref: neuronames:1273\nxref: NLX:144468\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"MBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001897 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! dorsal plus ventral thalamus\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002788 {source=\"MBA\"} ! anterior nuclear group\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035975\nname: intergeniculate leaflet of the lateral geniculate complex\nsynonym: \"IGL\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [MBA:27]\nsynonym: \"intergeniculate leaflet of the lateral geniculate complex\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1956]\nsynonym: \"intergeniculate leaflet, lateral geniculate complex\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1956]\nsynonym: \"lateral geniculate complex, intergeniculate leaflet\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1956]\nxref: MBA:27\nxref: neuronames:1956\nxref: NLX:144470\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"MBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001926 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! lateral geniculate body\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035999\nname: dopaminergic cell groups\ndef: \"Collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter dopamine ( Fuxe-1970 ).\" [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"DA cell groups\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"dopaminergic cell groups\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"dopaminergic nuclei\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nxref: neuronames:3138\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000700 ! dopaminergic neuron\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036012\nname: nucleus of the brachium of the inferior colliculus\nsynonym: \"brachial nucleus of the inferior colliculus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1112]\nsynonym: \"BrC\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [HBA:9483]\nsynonym: \"NB\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [MBA:580]\nsynonym: \"nucleus brachium inferior colliculus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1112]\nsynonym: \"nucleus of the brachium of the inferior colliculus\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1112]\nxref: HBA:9483\nxref: MBA:580\nxref: neuronames:1112\nxref: NLX:144476\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"HBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002314 {source=\"HBA\"} ! midbrain tectum\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036044\nname: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIAf\nsynonym: \"CbVIIa1\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [DHBA:12846]\nsynonym: \"lobule VIIAf/crus I (folium and superior semilunar lobule)\" EXACT [DHBA:12846]\nsynonym: \"VIIAf\" EXACT OMO:0003000 [HBA:4706]\nxref: DHBA:12846\nxref: HBA:4706\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"DHBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0004009 {source=\"HBA\"} ! cerebellum posterior vermis\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036065\nname: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIAt\nsynonym: \"CbVIIa2\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [DHBA:12847]\nsynonym: \"lobule VIIAt/crus II (tuber and inferior semilunar lobule)\" EXACT [DHBA:12847]\nsynonym: \"VIIAt\" EXACT OMO:0003000 [HBA:4707]\nxref: DHBA:12847\nxref: HBA:4707\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"DHBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0004002 {source=\"DHBA\"} ! posterior lobe of cerebellum\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0004009 {source=\"HBA\"} ! cerebellum posterior vermis\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036164\nname: ambient gyrus\ndef: \"A rostral part of the parahippocampal gyrus.\" [NeuroNames:2072]\nsynonym: \"AG\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [DHBA:12166]\nsynonym: \"ambiens gyrus\" EXACT [DHBA:12166]\nsynonym: \"gyrus ambiens\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [DHBA:12166]\nsynonym: \"limen insula\" RELATED [NeuroNames:2072]\nxref: DHBA:12166\nxref: neuronames:2072\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"DHBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0034773 {source=\"DHBA\"} ! uncus of parahippocampal gyrus\nproperty_value: terminology_notes \"Some authors regard it as part of the gyrus underlying the uncus ( Ture-1999 ), others as a synonym for limen insula.\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036218\nname: secondary prosencephalon\ndef: \"The most anterior region of the forebrain including both the telencephalon and the hypothalamus in the prosomeric model.\" [DOI:10.1111/dgd.12348, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1322]\ncomment: may contain the optic recess region (ORR) in the new model proposed by Yamamoto et al. 2017 (see https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28470718)\nsynonym: \"SP\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [DMBA:15567]\nxref: DMBA:15567\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 {source=\"DMBA\"} ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001890 {source=\"DMBA\", source=\"DOI:10.1111/dgd.12348\"} ! forebrain\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2000603\nname: valvula cerebelli\ndef: \"Brain structure which is caudally attached to the rostral medulla oblongata and extends into the tectal ventricle. The valvula cerebelli consists of a granular and a molecular layer along with aggregations of large Purkinje and eurydendroid cells and is uniquely present in ray-finned fishes. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.\" [ISBN:3764351209, ZFA:0000603, ZFA:curator]\nsynonym: \"valvula\" RELATED [ZFA:0000603]\nsynonym: \"valvula cerebellum\" EXACT OMO:0003004 [TAO:0000603, ZFA:0000603]\nxref: TAO:0000603\nxref: ZFA:0000603\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:32443 {contributor=\"michaelerice\", source=\"PMID:2040726\"} ! Teleostei\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002037 {source=\"ZFA\"} ! cerebellum\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (teleost_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/tao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2002106\nname: eminentia granularis\ndef: \"Anatomical structure that is a subdivision of the cerebellum; it is the location of some lateral line nerve synapses.\" [TAO:wd]\ncomment: Definition based on Albert,2001 [Albert JS. 2001. Species Diversity and Phylogenetic systematics of American Knifefishes (Gymnotiformes, Teleostei). Miscellaneous Publications, Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan no. 190:140 pages.]\nsynonym: \"EG\" EXACT [TAO:0002106]\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002037 ! cerebellum\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (teleost_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/tao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2002107\nname: medullary command nucleus\ndef: \"Anatomical structure that consists of two neuron types: pacemaker cells and relay cells. The medullary command nucleus commands the timing of the electric organ discharge.\" [TAO:wd]\ncomment: Definition reference: Moortgat, KT, Bullock, TH, and Sejnowski TJ. 2000. J Neurophysiol 83: 971-983. Precision of the Pacemaker Nucleus in a Weakly Electric Fish: Network Versus Cellular Influences.\nsynonym: \"MCN\" EXACT [TAO:0002107]\nsynonym: \"medullary pacemaker nucleus\" EXACT [TAO:0002107]\nsynonym: \"pacemaker nucleus\" EXACT [TAO:0002107]\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002028 ! hindbrain\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (teleost_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/tao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440015\nname: noradrenergic cell groups\ndef: \"Collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter norepinephrine (noradrenalin).\" [WikipediaVersioned:Noradrenergic_cell_groups&oldid=965992184]\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000459 ! noradrenergic cell\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440024\nname: visceral area\ndef: \"A cortical area between the agranular insular cortex and the supplemental somatosensory area in rats and mice. The VISC is the architectonically equivalent structure granular insula in humans.\" [neuronames:1192&questID=2709]\nsynonym: \"VISC\" EXACT [MBA:677]\nxref: MBA:677\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: dorsal_to UBERON:0034893 ! agranular insular cortex\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:9989 ! Rodentia\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\nrelationship: ventral_to UBERON:0008934 ! secondary somatosensory cortex\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440025\nname: parapyramidal nucleus\ndef: \"A small group of cells located lateral to the pyramid of the medulla in the rat and the mouse that functionally it belongs to the reticular formation of the subcortical motor system.\" [neuronames:1771]\nsynonym: \"PPY\" EXACT [MBA:1069]\nxref: MBA:1069\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002298 ! brainstem\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440032\nname: prelimbic area\ndef: \"A region in the medial prefrontal cortex that is dorsal to the infralimbic area important in expression of conditioned reward and fear behaviour.\" [PMID:30850668]\nsynonym: \"PL\" EXACT [MBA:972]\nsynonym: \"prelimbic cortex\" EXACT [PMID:30639183]\nsynonym: \"PrL\" EXACT [PMID:30639183]\nxref: MBA:972\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: dorsal_to UBERON:8440033 ! infralimbic area\nrelationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440033 ! infralimbic area\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000451 ! prefrontal cortex\nrelationship: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9989 ! Rodentia\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440033\nname: infralimbic area\ndef: \"A region in the medial prefrontal cortex that is ventral to the prelimbic area important in supression of conditioned reward and fear behaviour.\" [PMID:30850668]\nsynonym: \"IL (brain)\" EXACT [PMID:30639183]\nsynonym: \"ILA\" EXACT [MBA:44]\nsynonym: \"infralimbic cortex\" EXACT [PMID:30639183]\nxref: MBA:44\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440032 ! prelimbic area\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000451 ! prefrontal cortex\nrelationship: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9989 ! Rodentia\nrelationship: ventral_to UBERON:8440032 ! prelimbic area\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440039\nname: piriform-amygdalar area\ndef: \"The cortical region between the cortical amygdalar area and the piriform area.\" [MBA:788]\ncomment: In the human and macaque, the piriform-amygdalar area is not distinguished from the postpiriform transition area. {xref=\"neuronames:1776\"}\nsynonym: \"PAA (brain)\" EXACT [MBA:788]\nxref: MBA:788\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440040\nname: dorsal peduncular area\ndef: \"A cytoarchitectonic area on the medial surface of the cerebral hemisphere rostral to the septum, ventral to the infralimbic area and dorsal to the tenia tecta in the mouse and rat.\" [neuronames:1776]\ncomment: Some authors regard it not as a separate structure but as the ventral part of the infralimbic area. {xref=\"neuronames:1776\"}\nsynonym: \"DP\" EXACT [MBA:814]\nxref: MBA:814\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440075\nname: gustatory cortex\ndef: \"The part of the cerebral cortex that is responsible for the perception of taste.\" [WikipediaVersioned:Gustatory_cortex&oldid=1048584788]\nsynonym: \"gustatory area\" EXACT [MBA:1057]\nxref: MBA:1057\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7258-9596 ! Shawn Zheng Kai Tan\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001033 ! gustatory system\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440076\nname: somatomotor area\ndef: \"A part of the cerebral cortex that comprises of the primary motor cortex and the premotor cortex.\" [MBA:500]\nxref: MBA:500\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7258-9596 ! Shawn Zheng Kai Tan\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0001384 ! primary motor cortex\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0016634 ! premotor cortex\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
